<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-475] Add note about lfs syntax changes for Lustre 2.6</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-475</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In the lfs sections 40.1.1, 40.1.3 and 40.1.4 of the Lustre manual, we reference &#8220;lfs quotacheck &#8230;&#8221; and &#8220;lfa quotaon &#8230;&#8221;, but on master, these lfs options don&#8217;t exist. &#8216;setquota&#8217; and &#8216;quota&#8217; are the only valid LFS options dealing with quota.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;LFS options&#160; was removed &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/14705/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/14705/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Add a condition to a text box like &quot;Starting in Lustre 2.6, the ... commands were removed, and ... should be used instead.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
